divs: Sighting DetailsWe were on our rooftop deck for lunch - we noticed an egg-shaped white object moving directly vertical in the sky. It seemed to slightly wave back and forth, but it was not a balloon. It then moved in a straight line east-ward, and after about five minutes, moved straight up again. We took a picture of it, and upon magnification it seems to be divided into three sections. (See attached image) We were in downtown Toronto (Leslieville area), ON Canada, on Saturday, Sept 19, 2009 at approximately 2:00pm. We saw the object for approx 10 minutes in total.
Summary: White (or metallic) egg-like shape in sky, with possibly 3 sections, moving up, then east, then up again
Object Flight Path: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
